cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the performance of inter-vehicular communication networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a pilot estimation technique to reduce the bit error rate, which involves the use of information theory concepts. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with improving the quality of communication in vehicular networks, which is a sub-domain of communications and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a solution to overcome the mobility problem of terminal communication, which involves the use of control systems. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of rearranging pilot symbol positions on the quality of transmission, which is related to multimedia signal processing.
